Raymart is a talented full-stack web developer with a passion for creating easy-to-use, accessible web applications. With a deep understanding of web development technologies, he has established himself as a leader in the field, and has been recognized for his expertise and dedication.

He enjoys teaching web development and is always willing to lend a helping hand to those who want to learn.

Raymart specializes in turning web designs into functional code that can be used to create high-quality websites and web applications. Although he has experience in web design, his true passion lies in coding. biography_description:
Edgar "Ivan" Dela Cruz, a humble citizen of Sampaloc, Manila, grew up as an only child in a small but modest and religiously devout neighborhood near the slums of the fourth district. Because of his upbringing and environment, he has devoted most of his youth to philanthropic initiatives. 

He once was an altar server and a charity knight where he administered organization-related events in online learning, served every Sunday mass and high ceremonial celebrations, did off-parish external outreach, conducted external outreach programs and networks with other endowed NGOs to volunteer in community services such as feeding programs, educational programs, prayer vigils, fund-raising activities every single week. He also took part in the Crew and Outfit programs of the Senior Boy Scout of the Philippines.

When he started to explore the multimedia world after hearing about it being described as the best path for artists who are unsure of which art form he/she would find gratifying, he eventually got his grasp of self-awareness. He chose this college program because he was always so fascinated in filmmaking as to why he began creating real and entry-level art. Sometimes outstanding, sometimes not, what he made sure is he does learn despite the financial hardships. With fairly enough experience in freelancing and taking part-time jobs, he made it possible to continue his studies. As some kind of hobby and leisure, he finds a number of self-improvement books fun to learn in his downtime. Marketing, finance, and some branches of science are only a few of the disciplines he dives into. Treading unfamiliar territories is quite likely an adrenaline shot for him because tackling different industries is his aim, in order to not be confined to his major. Curiosity feeds the cat indeed, giving him an edge. Years go by and his interests also expanded. Now he is not only Inordinately knowledgeable in ConsumerTech, especially mobile computing, in Cycling consumerism, Advertising and Public Relations, he is also heavily indulged in  Media and Mass Communication, and is also appreciative in Gaming Industry wherein he actually used to play competitively. More than that, he now records his own music to perform it live in gigs, and involves himself in streetwear modelling as he has also become decently insightful in Music Industry and become deeply interested in Fashion industry. Locked in and loaded, he views these interests as his Ikigai. 

Provision of industry-standard creatives like static and videographic publication materials through the formulation of his own design ideas with the maintenance of the company's brand identity is his prospectus in the creative industry. Experiences as an organization officer and his past ventures made him the Ivan that he is, and as of today, he is currently in search of a position in various disciplines of creation where he can develop his skills with the experience he delves into. Employ him anywhere in he will thrive like a green leaf, no matter how slow. He believes that to attain his goals, striving for it is what is needed in the beginning. Being excellent under a workforce is essentially what everyone should experience to be able to reach his dreams, which is why he is more than ready to make great use of his skills and talents.

biography_title: From Aspiring IT Student to IT Professional
biography_description:
Christian Paul D. Dayag is a 23-year-old IT student at Mabalacat City College (MCC) who is passionate about pursuing a career in the IT industry. Growing up, Christian had a keen interest in technology and was always curious about how things worked. As a result, Christian decided to pursue a degree in IT to learn more about this exciting field.

Throughout Christian's academic journey, He has developed a range of skills, including web development, graphic design using tools such as Photoshop and Canva, and voice-over work. Christian is also fluent in English. He has experience being ESL Teacher for over four years at Nativecamp Company, which has helped Him to communicate effectively with clients and colleagues from all around the world.

In His free time, Christian enjoys playing the guitar and drums, playing games, and basketball. He finds that these hobbies help Him to relax and unwind after a busy day of studying or working on projects.

Looking ahead, Christian is excited about the opportunities that the IT industry holds and is determined to work hard to become a successful IT professional. He is eager to use His skills and knowledge to make a positive impact on the world and help to create innovative solutions that can benefit society as a whole.
personal_characteristics:
Christian is a driven and focused individual, with a passion for both personal and professional growth. As a good listener, he is empathetic and attentive to others' perspectives, making him an excellent friend and colleague.

As an enthusiast, Christian approaches life with a sense of excitement and wonder, always eager to learn new things and take on new challenges. He is a strong believer in the importance of family and maintaining a healthy work-life balance and actively strives to achieve this balance in his own life.

Christian is a natural opportunity seeker, always on the lookout for new ways to grow and develop both personally and professionally. He has a strong entrepreneurial spirit and a keen sense of business acumen, making him a valuable asset to any team.

However, Christian can sometimes be quiet and reserved and may need more time to feel comfortable expressing his thoughts and ideas. He may also struggle with procrastination and occasional clumsiness, but takes these setbacks in stride and works to learn from his mistakes.

Despite occasional tendencies towards clinginess, Christian values his independence and is always striving to be the best version of himself.

course_description:
Bachelor of Science in Information Technology (BSIT) is an undergraduate program that focuses on the application of computing technologies to solve problems in different fields. The program is designed to provide students with a solid foundation in both the theoretical and practical aspects of information technology, including software development, database management, network administration, and web development.

In a BSIT program, students will learn about the different programming languages, algorithms, and data structures, as well as system analysis and design methodologies. The curriculum also covers essential topics such as computer architecture, operating systems, and computer networks.

Throughout the program, students will also develop problem-solving and critical thinking skills that are necessary to succeed in the field of information technology. They will be exposed to various real-world applications of technology and will be required to apply their knowledge and skills to solve complex problems.

Graduates of a BSIT program are well-equipped to pursue various careers in the field of technology, including software developers, network administrators, web developers, and IT project managers. They are also well-prepared to continue their education and pursue advanced degrees in computer science, information technology, or related fields.

biography_title: From Dreams to Reality: The Journey of Riel S. Guiwa - A Student's Path to Success in the World of IT
biography_description:
is a captivating biography that chronicles the inspiring life and accomplishments of Riel S. Guiwa, a determined and ambitious student hailing from Tarlac State University. This engaging narrative delves into the early aspirations and passion that sparked Riel's interest in the world of Information Technology and Digital Solutions.

Throughout the biography, readers embark on a transformative expedition, witnessing Riel's growth from a curious learner to an accomplished intern at iPhiTech IT and Digital Solution. The story unfolds, revealing the various challenges and triumphs that shaped Riel's journey. From overcoming obstacles to seizing opportunities, Riel's relentless pursuit of knowledge and excellence becomes evident as the driving force behind his success.

As the biography progresses, readers gain profound insights into Riel's experiences during his internship, providing valuable lessons for aspiring IT professionals. The biography weaves together heartwarming anecdotes, candid reflections, and valuable advice from mentors and colleagues, allowing readers to connect with Riel on a personal level and draw inspiration from his tenacity.

"From Dreams to Reality" also sheds light on the transformative impact of education, the significance of hands-on learning, and the power of perseverance. The biography highlights Riel's dedication to lifelong learning and his unwavering commitment to making a positive impact in the IT and Digital Solutions realm.

biography_description:
I got the opportunity to work as part of a team that is responsible with developing as well as maintaining of a web-based file management system. This experience not only improved my technical skills but also proved my ability to work successfully as part of a team.

In creating clear and visually appealing interfaces, we heavily used markup languages such as HTML and CSS. JavaScript was critical in increasing interactivity and responsiveness, making the system more user friendly and engaging. We also used PHP and MySQL to handle backend operations and data management. PHP enabled us to create strong and secure server side functionality, while MySQL ensured efficient data storage and retrieval, contributing to the system's overall performance.

The primary use of the website is to support users (admin)  in managing files and folders. They have the capacity to add files from their PC`s as well as create, rename, copy, edit, and remove files and folders. One of my task is to test and fixing any problems to ensure that these actions went without any issues. I made sure everything worked as it should and, if not, I worked out how to fix it. By doing this, I could guarantee the website's functionality and usability.

Through our collaborative efforts, we were able to enhance the file management system current features and successfully implement new functionality in alignment with user expectations. The project gave me valuable skills in solving issues, code optimization, and effective communication.

course_description:
I am a Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering graduate student. My academic experience has been extremely enjoyable, providing me with a solid foundation of knowledge as well as a major improvement in my programming skills. 

Exposure to the world of programming was one of the most eye-opening experiences I had in college. I've gained an in-depth knowledge of many programming languages, algorithms, data structures and database management through building system like inventory system, website and mobile application. Because of this experience, I am now able to write effective, well-organized code, and I have a strong desire to solve problems.

I also expanded my programming knowledge when we had a thesis project. The technology to develop our prototype includes Arduino IDE, Arduino Uno Board / ESP 32 and Sensors. These resources provide me the chance to learn about microcontrollers and sensors, as well as to work in a team and other people collaboratively. 

Our thesis's title is "RAINWATER AND RENEWABLE HYDROPOWER ENERGY HARVESTING AND MONITORING SYSTEM," and the prototype's functions are to collect rainwater from our roof, storing it in a water tank for later use, also using it to rotate a motor and propeller to generate electricity. The microcontrollers and sensors was used  to monitor the water level, water quality, voltage, and current and we use Arduino IDE and C++ as the programming language to program the microcontroller  to communicate to sensors and input/output devices like LCD I2C, LED`s, buttons. also use NODE RED to display the system condition (water level, water quality, voltage, and current) by connecting nodes and doing a little bit programming. In addition it can save the data sensor in a database, where we utilize PHPmyadmin (MySQL) to do it, in order to store, analyze and visualize the data sensor.  

I am eager to use my strong programming background to practical issues and help develop creative solutions. I am eager to go on a path that will enable me to continuously learn, advance, and make a significant contribution to the technology industry.

I am having a great time learning new things, and this makes me more excited about making incredible things web creation.
